<br>
Set a minimum value for each item. If more than 1 person wants an item, it is auctioned                      off. Whoever wants the item the most AND has the points to pay for it gets the item. In case of a tie, random and the winner pays the points. Auction can be done in guildchat or even over the *gasp* auction channel . If noone will pay the minimum, the item rots and the next time the minimum is lowered by 25% or .5 point, whichever is greater. This is to prevent people from not bidding on items until the price is dropped in order to get a cheaper price than what they are willing to pay for it..<br>
<br>
So UberDruid04 has 160 points saved up and UberPaladin has 130 points saved up. An All/All item drops worth 10 points normally. They both want the item however the paladin wants the item more. Under your system, the Druid would get the item and would be at 150 points while the paladin would be at 130. However if it was auctioned, the paladin might be willing to pay 15 points while the druid only 12. The item would get sold at 12.5 points to the paladin leaving the druid with 160 points and the paladin at 117.5. that extra 2.5 points that was spent on the item is the inefficiency of setting a price before the item drops.<br>
<br>
This system works because each point is equivalent.. much like cash, the druid has saved up 160 dollars and the paladin only 130. However they can both afford the item and the paladin is willing to pay more so he gets it. If some uber uber item drops and 20 people all want it, the person who is willing to pay the most gets the item.. not the person who has the most points. The mere fact that 20 people are willing to pay the same price for an item means that they are willing to pay more than that price.<br>
<br>
Anyhow I tried to convince my guild to go this route but they are deciding to go for a socialist like point system where everyone who puts in enough effort last week gets to roll this week. &quot;enough&quot; is arbitrary and its not as fair as a pure points system imho but what can you do *shrug*<br>
