Metopious <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uwendolynkeplegrobal.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wendolyn KeplegrobAL</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.wired-cafe.com/images/wendhead.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 40<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/18/01 9:10:27 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub114.ezboard.com/flegacyofsteel43089general.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=891.topic&index=53>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.wired-cafe.com/images/wendside.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Issues...</span><hr size=1> Aye... starting the system now when the guild has already been around for a while might cause some problems.<br>
<br>
And since the thread resurfaced I saw some questions that never got answered... regarding &quot;time spent&quot; at a raid: most of our raids are 1 shot deals... you show up any time before the kill and you get DKP.  This give ppl usually about a 1 hour window to get to a raid... with most people showing up on time or ~10-15 minutes late.  No one really complains about the ppl that might show up right before the dain pull... or that get a last second summon up to Yel.  However, if we notice a trend that one person seems to always show up at the last second...there would be repercussions.  For longer raids, like ToV farming or CT (where you need to clear the whole zone), DKP is broken down into segments.  ToV raids get DKP every 2 hours that we are there based on what had dropped in the those 2 hours. CT gives 0.7 DKP... and a clearing bonus was added for 0.3 if you were present from the time we zone in.<br>
<br>
Also, we have IDKP...which is incentive DKP.  This is awarded to ppl at raids where DKP might not normally have been given out... like Klandicar.  In order to provide a &quot;reason&quot; to come to raids like Klandicar, where no DKP loot drops, we give out IDKP to ppl that gets added to DKP total for lotto purposes.  <br>
<br>
Finally, we also give out special case DKP... in Sleeper's for example.  Not everyone has a key... and it's not fair that someone should miss out on raid DKP due how slow we obtain keys.  So when we go into Sleepers Tomb for raids, anyone that is online doing something productive for the guild (farming gems, trade components for guild, etc) will get DKP for each kill.  <br>
<br>
DKP is constantly evolving... it reacts much like an economy for item pricing... and it changes accordingly to game and raid dynamics. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#212141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uphaethondarkreaper.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Phaethon Darkreaper</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/18/01 9:49:26 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub114.ezboard.com/flegacyofsteel43089general.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=891.topic&index=54>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Issues...</span><hr size=1> How do you handle dkp for epic pieces Off big mobs? <p>I dunno, I just root & nuke...</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uwendolynkeplegrobal.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wendolyn KeplegrobAL</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.wired-cafe.com/images/wendhead.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 42<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/18/01 11:43:38 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub114.ezboard.com/flegacyofsteel43089general.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=891.topic&index=55>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.wired-cafe.com/images/wendside.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Issues...</span><hr size=1> You pay 20 DKP for your epic... with that 20 DKP you are guaranteed guild support to finish the &quot;harder&quot; parts of the epic quest.  Depending on the quest it can be broken down into 2 payments of 10... which normally end up being paid at the &quot;larger&quot; encounters that require support.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#212141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uwiggystabsalot.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wiggy Stabsalot</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.followmearound.com/images/artwork/lostchild.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 15<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/19/01 10:53:39 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub114.ezboard.com/flegacyofsteel43089general.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=891.topic&index=56>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Ahhhh</span><hr size=1> Oh Wendy, you meant THIS DKNY thread on LoS's board...right. Thanks <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><hr>
