<center><a href=http://www.3deearts.com/sos/profile.asp?who=Deleroache><b><font color=116622 size=+1>Deleroache "The Pathfinder" Blacksoule</a></b></font><BR>
<center><font color="red" size=+1>Warder<center></font></center>
<center></font><a href=http://pub8.ezboard.com/bsocietyofshadows><font color="green"><i>Society of Shadows</i></font></a><br><center><hr width=45%></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#212141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uwendolynkeplegrobal.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wendolyn KeplegrobAL</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.wired-cafe.com/images/wendhead.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 43<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/20/01 6:01:02 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub114.ezboard.com/flegacyofsteel43089general.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=891.topic&index=60>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.wired-cafe.com/images/wendside.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Economic Theory</span><hr size=1> Auctioning is not going to work... not for AL at least.  The whole purpose of DKP is to ensure those that participate the most get the items they want 1st.   Members don't attend every single raid to accumulate the most points just so they can lose out on an item to a over-zealous loot monger or be forced to spend more than they should.  They attend every raid so they can be guaranteed the item they want when it drops.  For example, the gnome illusion mask dropped in Sleepers for us.  Thott had around 160 DKP... the most DKP of any member by around +50.  Thott wants the mask.  It costs 1 DKP.  Looks like Thott will get the mask.  But wait! Another member wants the mask too... they have been in the guild 2 months and only have 30 DKP... but they are willing to spend ALL 30 on it for the mask! This would cause Thott to either a) lose the mask or b) spend 31 to get it.  There's no way this is ever going to be acceptable (in AL at least).  Thott wants the mask... Thott has the most DKP... thus Thott has earned and deserves the mask... without exception.  Our guild would not support a policy or system which allowed anything different from that.  <br>
<br>
IDKP is simple.  You get IDKP as compensation for your time at raids when there's no real &quot;loot&quot; or reason to give out DKP.  DKP is based entirely on loot... you can only receive DKP at an event where DKP was spent by a member.  So for example lets say we go to Zlandicar... and he drops 2 claws, gloves, heart, fraka, and zland talis.  Every twink has a claw that wants one so they both rot... no one in their right mind would pay DKP for the gloves so those are free... no one wants a heart that doesn't have one... no one has the faction to make shround from harla... and zland talis is a key to sleepers which is awarded free to a member.  The end result is that we just brought 30+ ppl to an event and no one spent any DKP.. thus no DKP can be give to those 30+ for attending.   This is a problem... and it started happening a LOT.  Also, there were some raids which no one wanted to go to but were needed to further the guild's cause... like Klandicar.  We needed sleeper's keys... but Kland doesn't drop any loot that would warrant DKP being spent... so there was low motivation for some members to attend an event that they would not be compensated for.  Thus, the birth of IDKP.  Failed raids where we kill nothing but learned something in the process... IDKP... exploration and testing of new zones as an entire guild... IDKP...  anything productive which didn't yield loot... IDKP.  <br>
<br>
When we run lottos, DKP + IDKP = Total points you get to enter a lotto with... and the original intent of the system still holds true:  Your loot, and how soon you get loot, is directly corrolated to how often you attend events.  <br>
<br>
EDIT: guests (i.e. potential members who have applied via email and have a sponsor), are added to the guild for /gu purposes at the start of raids.  They are often greeted with &quot;/gu Welcome gimp labor&quot; or &quot;/gu Hi fodder&quot;.  They receive DKP and IDKP just like any other player at a raid.  They are free to use that DKP to enter lottos and buy items.  However, non-dkp loot is not available to them... WW armor for example =&gt; guild only.... even if it's only going to a twink.  Sweat-shop workers must then /guildremove at the end of the night and thank us for all the DT's they took.   <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uwendolynkeplegrobal.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wendolyn KeplegrobAL</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.wired-cafe.com/images/wendhead.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10> at: 4/20/01 6:08:53 am<br></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page <a href=http://pub114.ezboard.com/flegacyofsteel43089general.showMessageRange?topicID=891.topic&start=1&stop=20>1</a><a href=http://pub114.ezboard.com/flegacyofsteel43089general.showMessageRange?topicID=891.topic&start=21&stop=40>2</a> <b>3</b> <a href=http://pub114.ezboard.com/flegacyofsteel43089general.showMessageRange?topicID=891.topic&start=61&stop=80>4</a><a href=http://pub114.ezboard.com/flegacyofsteel43089general.showMessageRange?topicID=891.topic&start=81&stop=100>5</a><a href=http://pub114.ezboard.com/flegacyofsteel43089general.showMessageRange?topicID=891.topic&start=101&stop=120>6</a><a href=http://pub114.ezboard.com/flegacyofsteel43089general.showMessageRange?topicID=891.topic&start=121&stop=133>7</a> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub114.ezboard.com/flegacyofsteel43089general.showPrevMessage?topicID=891.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub114.ezboard.com/flegacyofsteel43089general.showNextMessage?topicID=891.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br>